post_text:
Info on the High School LCU XC Meet on Saturday.
We will be running in Section 1 on Saturday morning with the boys starting at 8:30 and the girls following at 9. The bus will leave the school at 7:20. I have attached a Covid parking map provided by LCU which will detail where we will be. In years past, spectators entered the course by the LCHS Gym. I don't know if that is still the case or if they will have a designated area for spectators to enter and stay.
Per LCU:
**Parents/Fans can come but please encourage mask wearing. Same for your athletes when they are not warming up/racing. **
The JH races will have the same parking procedure except we will be in Section 4 with the boys starting at 7 pm and the girls following at 7:03, yes, 7:03. The bus will leave the school at 6 pm.

post_text: Today's New Home High School Class of 2020 spotlight - Riley Stokes, the daughter of Ronnie and Stacy Stokes. Throughout her time at New Home, Riley has been a Lynn Co. 4-H Ambassador, FFA Chapter Officer, Varsity Mascot, and National Honor Society President. Riley has been very competitive in many organizations such as 4-H, FFA, stock shows, the Texas Alliance for Minorities in Engineering, and Science Fair having competed on the state level in all of these organizations. She plans to attend Texas Tech University in the fall to study Civil Engineering and eventually earn her master’s degree.

post_text: A message from Mr. Fiedler
text: A message from Mr. Fiedler

post_text:
To the parents of New Home ISD:

By now I am sure you are aware of the closings of multiple schools in our area. I want to take a moment to let you know that our administration team has been in constant contact with multiple districts in our area, state school officials, and members of our medical community in order to provide the best education possible in a safe and secure setting. We have called for an emergency board meeting this Thursday evening to address some of the issues that we are currently facing. I ask that you please be patient as we work through these un-chartered waters. You can expect an announcement regarding our plans for Monday at the conclusion of our board meeting.

Thank you,

Shane Fiedler

post_text: Per Mrs. Quillin in response to a picture question...Hi, everyone! Let me fill you in on what is going on. Lifetouch sent me some pictures, and when I received the shipment, I realized it was not all of what we should have received. I called them, and they said they have a new system, and the online orders would be mailed to homes. They asked that I fill the campus orders with what they sent me. I did that, and then waited (patiently?) for them to mail the rest. It became apparent that this was not happening, so I started to fill the rest of the orders as people requested them with what I had left. So, now I am completely out of pictures and in need of more from Lifetouch. I am trying to fix Lifetouch’s error as much as possible for our parents and students, but it is just a mess! Please just email me if you still need one, and I will do my best to get it to you ASAP. Please email me at jquillin@esc17.net. There is no way I can keep up with all of the FB messages, Remind, GroupMe, etc. without missing one, so please email me! Thanks!

post_text: This post is a little late since we were waiting on awards and people who have been out, but we want to make sure we acknowledge these kids, albeit late. Mrs. Walker took a group of students to the TAME Math and Science Competition in January 28, and our NH kids dominated! The placings are too numerous to list here, but we are proud of each and every one of them, and extremely proud of our state qualifiers: Trey Evans, Whit Smithson, Sam Kirkland, and Zac Ford. Way to go, Leopards!

post_text: New Home TAME Club represented well today in Amarillo at the egg drop competition. The Winners(Zac Ford, Jaden Hollinshead, and Whit Smithson) placed 3rd in the high school division. Humpty Dumpy(Connor Cook, Mia Williams, Casen Lucas, Brooklyn Smith, and Jaxxon Zant) placed 2nd in the high school division. Crackin' Down the CompEGGtition(Courtney Jackson, Danielle Fonseca, Dillan Ford, and Alice Hamilton) brought home the lean green egg machine trophy for the most recycled project in the high school division. Kaden Gray, Hunter Watkins, Cameron McFadden, and Noah Mojica brought home the trophy for the most innovative project in the junior high division. And finally Sabrina Multer and Kristi Walker won the teacher division.
text: New Home TAME Club represented well today in Amarillo at the egg drop competition. The Winners(Zac Ford, Jaden Hollinshead, and Whit Smithson) placed 3rd in the high school division. Crackin' Down the CompEGGtition(Courtney Jackson, Danielle Fonseca, Dillan Ford, and Alice Hamilton) brought home the lean green egg machine trophy for the most recycled project in the high school division. Kaden Gray, Hunter Watkins, Cameron McFadden, and Noah Mojica brought home the trophy for the most innovative project in the junior high division. And finally Sabrina Multer and Kristi Walker won the teacher division.

post_text: As we close the book on another year, here are some pics and results from the State Track Meet in Austin. Jasmine and Jacie jumped and vaulted on Friday with Jasmine placing 8th and Jacie placing 4th. The 800 relay was supposed to run at 1:25 on Saturday but Mother Nature had other plans and after 7 long hours, the girls (Chelsi, Katherine, DD and Jasmine) finally ran and placed 6th. One good thing about the delay is that it backed our session into the night session so 1A & 4A were stacked in between 2A & 6A so the stadium was packed and electric. Definately the biggest crowd they had ever ran in front of. Overall, a great trip!!!

post_text: A week after their strong showing at District, the Lady Leopards ended the day as the Area Runner's Up behind Anton. They qualified 2nd place relay teams in the 400, 800 and 1600 meter relays as well as runners in the 100 & 200 and in the field events, a pole vaulter, high jumper, triple jumper and two long jumpers. Great job and Good Luck at the Regional Track Meet.
text: A week after their strong showing at District, the Lady Leopards ended the day as the Area Runner's Up behind Anton. They qualified 2nd place relay teams in the 400, 800 and 1600 meter relays as well as runners in the 100 & 200 and in the field events, a pole vaulter, high jumper, triple jumper and two long jumpers. The Leopards continued to roll as well capturing relay titles in the 800 and 1600 meter relays. They also qualified individuals in the 400, 300 hurdles and 200. Great job and Good Luck at the Regional Track Meet.
